cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method that uses a fully convolutional neural network (FCNN) to enhance the accuracy of deformable registration algorithms in medical image analysis. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of FCNN suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the application of the method to 3D brain MRI data sets suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
